docs.abstract: It’s a scary time for body-based art. What will survive after the pandemic? As dance artists fight the old ways, a new empowerment is in the air.
docs.snippet: It’s a scary time for body-based art. What will survive after the pandemic? As dance artists fight the old ways, a new empowerment is in the air.
docs.lead_paragraph: When the coronavirus pandemic started, the first thing I did was panic. I didn’t want to bum anyone out, but it didn’t take me long to leap to a certain conclusion: With theaters and studios shutting down, the dance world would be devastated. What would come out of the ashes?

headline.main: Could Dance Be a Weapon All Over Again?
headline.print_headline: Dance Is in Ashes. Time to Arise.

docs.abstract: Great-great-grandchildren of Jefferson Davis, Stonewall Jackson and Robert E. Lee disagree with President Trump that moving Confederate monuments destroys American history and culture.
docs.snippet: Great-great-grandchildren of Jefferson Davis, Stonewall Jackson and Robert E. Lee disagree with President Trump that moving Confederate monuments destroys American history and culture.
docs.lead_paragraph: The year is 2017, and as the president of the United States vehemently defends monuments to the Confederacy, some descendants of Confederate leaders are calling for them to be taken down.

headline.main: Confederate Leaders’ Descendants Say Statues Can Come Down
headline.print_headline: Descendants Say Confederate Statues Can Go

docs.abstract: Barbara Underwood has served as the big thinker for a succession of bosses. Now, with the resignation of her last boss, she is stepping into the spotlight.
docs.snippet: Barbara Underwood has served as the big thinker for a succession of bosses. Now, with the resignation of her last boss, she is stepping into the spotlight.
docs.lead_paragraph: Despite a life of firsts — first in her law-school class, the first woman to serve as the nation’s solicitor general and now the first to serve as New York State’s attorney general — Barbara D. Underwood has spent most of her career as a No. 2.

headline.main: Replacing Schneiderman: A ‘Brilliant’ Lawyer Who Worked Behind the Scenes

docs.abstract: With Parliament considering a security bill, officers used tear gas and dispersal grenades in their response to a camp set up in a prominent square to protest against a lack of housing.
docs.snippet: With Parliament considering a security bill, officers used tear gas and dispersal grenades in their response to a camp set up in a prominent square to protest against a lack of housing.
docs.lead_paragraph: PARIS — The police cleared out a temporary migrant camp in central Paris, forcing people out of tents, chasing them in the streets and firing tear gas in a crackdown that fueled growing outrage over the government’s tough new security policies.

headline.main: Outcry in France After Police Clear Paris Migrant Camp
headline.print_headline: ‘I Was Stunned’: Outcry as Paris Police Dispel Migrant Camp

docs.abstract: Democrats can’t promote progressive policies while catering to the wealthy.
docs.snippet: Democrats can’t promote progressive policies while catering to the wealthy.
docs.lead_paragraph: Democratic politicians and strategists identify a “suburban revolt” against President Trump and right-wing Republican extremism as the key to victory in the 2018 and 2020 elections. They point to Democratic successes in the off-year 2017 elections in Virginia and New Jersey, and the surprise triumph of Senator Doug Jones in Alabama, as evidence for the party’s plan to target college-educated white women, upper-middle-class moderates and even disillusioned conservatives in the affluent suburbs.

headline.main: Turning Affluent Suburbs Blue Isn’t Worth the Cost
headline.print_headline: Turning Rich Suburbs Blue Isn’t Worth the Cost

docs.lead_paragraph: The new “West Side Story” begins with nothingness: a huge black brick wall rising behind a cavernous blank stage. A group of young people enter, walking slowly, surveying the territory. They form a line at the lip of the stage and stare at the audience.
